---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "Home";
const description = "AI workflows for small businesses that reduce overwhelm by improving how information flows through your business.";
---

<BaseLayout title={pageTitle} description={description}>

  <!-- ===== Hero ===== -->
  <section class="pt-10 pb-6 fade-in">
    <div class="text-[0.7rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-6" style="color: var(--text-tertiary);">
      Borgart
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-[2.1rem] font-light tracking-tight leading-[1.35] fade-in fade-in-d1" style="color: var(--text-primary); letter-spacing: -0.025em;">
      AI workflows for small businesses that <strong class="font-semibold">reduce overwhelm</strong> by improving how information flows through your business.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-[1.05rem] leading-relaxed max-w-[520px] fade-in fade-in-d2" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
      I help you find the most painful points in your documents, email, and follow-ups, then design simple workflows your team can run with confidence.
    </p>
    <div class="gradient-line mt-6 fade-in fade-in-d3"></div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== Class Announcement ===== -->
  <div class="pb-6">
    <div class="cta-block">
      <div class="text-[0.68rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4 relative" style="color: var(--text-tertiary);">
        Upcoming class
      </div>
      <img
        src="/ai-class-context-is-bridge.jpg"
        alt="Context is the bridge — from mess to sense"
        style="width: 100%; margin: 0 auto 24px; display: block; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border-light);"
      />
      <div class="text-[0.68rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3 relative" style="color: var(--text-tertiary);">
        Practical AI for Small Business
      </div>
      <div class="text-[1.05rem] font-semibold mb-3 relative leading-snug" style="color: var(--text-primary);">
        AI works better when it has context.
      </div>
      <p class="text-[0.88rem] leading-[1.7] relative mb-5" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
        Bring one annoying, repetitive business task and see how AI can use the real material your business already has.
      </p>
      <div class="text-[0.88rem] leading-[1.7] relative mb-5" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
        July 1, 2026 | 3–4 PM ET<br />
        Register: igmanagementgroup.org/ai-class
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 relative">
        <a
          href="https://us06web.zoom.us/meeting/register/iq27OR98TU67qfqCFmeOyA#/registration"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="px-6 py-3 rounded-md text-[0.88rem] font-medium text-center transition hover:opacity-80"
          style="background: var(--text-primary); color: var(--bg);"
        >
          Register for AI Knows Business Class
        </a>
        <a
          href="/ai-class-info"
          class="px-6 py-3 rounded-md text-[0.88rem] font-medium text-center transition hover:opacity-80"
          style="border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--text-primary);"
        >
          More Information
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ===== Is this you? ===== -->
  <section class="py-8 fade-in fade-in-d3" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border-light);">
    <div class="text-[0.7rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-6" style="color: var(--text-tertiary);">
      Is this you?
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div>
        <div class="text-[0.95rem] font-medium mb-1" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Scattered client and project documents</div>
        <p class="text-[0.88rem] leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">You dig through folders, emails, and shared drives to remember what you did for a client or what you promised.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="text-[0.95rem] font-medium mb-1" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Leads and follow-ups slipping through the cracks</div>
        <p class="text-[0.88rem] leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">Quotes go out, but follow-ups don't always happen. Renewals and check-ins are easy to forget when things get busy.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="text-[0.95rem] font-medium mb-1" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Too much information, not enough time</div>
        <p class="text-[0.88rem] leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">You're flooded with emails, notes, and updates, and it's hard to tell what actually needs your attention.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="text-[0.95rem] font-medium mb-1" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Social media keeps getting shoved aside</div>
        <p class="text-[0.88rem] leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">You know you should have a steady presence, but posts always fall to the bottom of the list.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== What I do ===== -->
  <section class="py-8" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border-light);">
    <div class="text-[0.7rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color: var(--text-tertiary);">
      What I do
    </div>
    <p class="text-[0.95rem] leading-[1.7]" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
      I focus on information workflows — the way information is captured, stored, and used inside your business. That means documents, email, notes, client histories, follow-up reminders. Most businesses have all of this scattered around, and the cost is real: time lost looking for things, decisions made without the full picture, work falling through the cracks.
    </p>
    <p class="text-[0.95rem] leading-[1.7] mt-4" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
      I start simple. We look at where you feel the most overwhelmed, pick one clear pain point, and design something straightforward to address it. I only add tools where there's an obvious, immediate benefit — tools cost both money and attention, and the goal is to reduce your load, not pile more on.
    </p>
    <p class="text-[0.95rem] leading-[1.7] mt-4" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
      I'm cautious about technology for its own sake. If a simpler approach works, we use it. If something requires a subscription or training, we make sure it's worth it before committing.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== Page links ===== -->
  <section class="py-8" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border-light);">
    <div class="space-y-1">
      <a href="/courses" class="list-item">
        <span class="text-[0.88rem]" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">Courses</span>
        <span class="text-[0.78rem]" style="color: var(--text-tertiary);">→</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/how-i-work" class="list-item">
        <span class="text-[0.88rem]" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">How I work</span>
        <span class="text-[0.78rem]" style="color: var(--text-tertiary);">→</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/about" class="list-item">
        <span class="text-[0.88rem]" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">About</span>
        <span class="text-[0.78rem]" style="color: var(--text-tertiary);">→</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/companion-ai" class="list-item">
        <span class="text-[0.88rem]" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">Companion AI</span>
        <span class="text-[0.78rem]" style="color: var(--text-tertiary);">→</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/contact" class="list-item" style="border-bottom: none;">
        <span class="text-[0.88rem]" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">Contact</span>
        <span class="text-[0.78rem]" style="color: var(--text-tertiary);">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
